The paper focuses on spectral graph convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning for tasks such as image classification and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the transferability of filters between different graphs, which is a topic related to generalization and robustness in machine learning, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with graph theory and topology, which could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
